<div id="review_147193313" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/147193313" />
    <a title="Hafidha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1953135-hafidha"><img alt="Hafidha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1304401216p2/1953135.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/147193313?book_show_action=true">Feb 09, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hafidha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hafidha" href="/user/show/1953135-hafidha">Hafidha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1953135-hafidha?shelf=childrens-books">childrens-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer147193313" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2449463905815294094">I wish I had a dollar for every time I&apos;ve read this book because my 2 year old cannot get enough of it. It was a gift for her 2nd birthday and hardly a day has gone by since that we&apos;ve not read it to her. It&apos;s a bit long so initially Kidlet would flip through the pages before I could finish reading it, but after four months, she sits through it and waits for her favorite parts. She even learned the cadence of the words, so when she asks for it we recognize more the rhythm than the actual words s</span>
  <span id="freeText2449463905815294094" style="display:none">I wish I had a dollar for every time I've read this book because my 2 year old cannot get enough of it. It was a gift for her 2nd birthday and hardly a day has gone by since that we've not read it to her. It's a bit long so initially Kidlet would flip through the pages before I could finish reading it, but after four months, she sits through it and waits for her favorite parts. She even learned the cadence of the words, so when she asks for it we recognize more the rhythm than the actual words she says. It's a clever book and I have come to really enjoy it. Kidlet juts out her "knobbly knees, turned out toes," and nose for me to tap when I get to those parts of the story, and she loves when I tickle her back with "purple prickles." </span>
  <a data-text-id="2449463905815294094" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


